        "description": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is derived from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model integrated along Lagrangian particle tracks, yielding a dimensionless ratio referenced to predicate device hemolysis. This QoI is the accepted regulatory metric for comparative hemolysis assessment in FDA guidance. Gradation 2: QoI is directly relevant to the COU decision criterion."
      },
